AVIAN INFLUENZA, HUMAN (26): BANGLADESH (DHAKA)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 29 Feb 2012
Source: Avian Flu Diary [summ., edited]
http://afludiary.blogspot.com/2012/02/bangladesh-reporting-their-4th-h5n1.html


A 40 year old male has been diagnosed as 4th case of human avian influenza A/(H5N1) influenza virus infection in Bangladesh. This case has been reported from live bird market surveillance system in Dhaka City on Sun 26 Feb 2012 (http://www.iedcr.org/images/pdf/Website-Notification-H5N1-280212.pdf). This was confirmed by rRT-PCR. The patient is a live bird market worker.

The case presented with cough. Throat and nasal swabs were collected and found positive for H5N1. Presently he is free from symptoms. IEDCR [Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control & Research] and ICDDR,B [International Centre for Diarrhoeal Disease Research, Bangladesh] are jointly investigating the case and monitoring the situation.

In Bangladesh the 1st case was detected in 2008, 2nd and 3rd cases were found in 2011.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[If confirmed by the World Health Organisation, this case will be the 4th to have been reported from Bangladesh. The symptoms of this case appear to be mild, and all 3 of the previous cases in Bangladesh survived infection.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Bangladesh showing the location Dhaka can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1VpI. - Mod.CP]
